SIMPLE: harlotry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Harlotry
<hw>Har"lot*ry</hw> <pr>(-r⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Ribaldry; buffoonery; a ribald story.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Piers Plowman.</au> <au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The trade or practice of prostitution; habitual or
customary lewdness.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Anything meretricious; <as>as, <ex>harlotry</ex> in
art</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A harlot; a strumpet; a baggage.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He sups to-night with a <qex>harlotry</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Harm</ent>⟦br⟧
